      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PURFECT LINE (1) showed good early speed and raced just off the lead before lifting to score with a bit up his sleeve at Kingscote last start. Munro sticks with the 3kg claim. Well placed to make it two on the bounce. STOLEN KISS (6) resumes and it's worth noting she filled a minor placing when returning from a spell last prep over 1050m at this track. Has been readied with a jump-out here and gets a key booking in Neindorf. Genuine threat. FLIRT (5) was bounced straight back to the winner's circle after a 35-day freshen, showing plenty of ticker to score by a nose. Is drawn to advantage and should be in this for a very long way. POWER OF TIME (3) accounted for a maiden field over 1050m at Balaklava last start. Re-unites with Pannell who was on board last start. Harder task ahead this time but can measure up. ALAA PLENTY (2) progressed nicely second-up when living up to market expectation and scoring by a head at Werribee. Gets in light with the claim and can keep the ball rolling.",
